DELIVER
  Set automatic per-sector delivery for a commodity each update.

SYNTAX
  deliver <commodity> <sects> <threshold> <direction>
  deli    <commodity> <sects> <threshold> <direction>

DESCRIPTION
  Configures a sector to automatically move a commodity in a given
  direction each update when the stockpile exceeds the threshold.
  Delivery is point-to-point and moves commodities one step.

  <commodity>  - single letter: f=food c=civ m=mil i=iron etc.
  <sects>      - sector spec; supports realm (#N) and ?des=X condition
  <threshold>  - don't deliver if stockpile is below this level
  <direction>  - hex direction or $ for distribution center:
                   u  upper-right      j  right
                   n  lower-right      b  lower-left
                   g  left             y  upper-left
                   $  to dist center   .  cancel delivery

  The ?des=X condition must be attached directly to <sects> with no
  space: #1?des=a not #1 ?des=a.

  Delivery uses sector mobility.  Distribution (see info threshold)
  is usually preferred since it uses less mobility.

EXAMPLE
  deliver f 7,-1 200 $          deliver food above 200 to dist center
  deliver i -4,2 50 j           deliver iron above 50 rightward
  deliver f * 0 .               cancel all food delivery
  deliver f #1?des=a 200 $      all agri in realm 1 deliver food
  deliver i *?des=m 100 $       all iron mines deliver to dist center

